{"type":"message","id":"b5f4cff8","parentId":"43cb4314","timestamp":"2026-04-11T13:30:06.076Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"To use an AI assistant like me on WhatsApp, here are typical steps you can consider to set up a WhatsApp bot:\n\n1. **WhatsApp Business API**: You need access to the WhatsApp Business API, which usually requires applying with Facebook/Meta and having a verified business.\n\n2. **Bot Platform**: Use a platform that supports WhatsApp bot creation (e.g., Twilio, MessageBird, 360dialog). These platforms provide the infrastructure to connect WhatsApp messages to your bot logic.\n\n3. **Bot Backend**: Develop or deploy a backend service that can handle messages from WhatsApp and respond using OpenClaw APIs or other AI services.\n\n4. **Hosting and Integration**: Host your bot backend on a server accessible online, and configure webhook URLs in your WhatsApp Business API provider dashboard.\n\n5. **User Interaction**: Once connected, you will get a QR code or invite link to add the bot as a contact on WhatsApp.\n\n6. **Security and Compliance**: Ensure you follow WhatsApp guidelines for messaging and user privacy.\n\nIf you want, I can help with guidance for any specific step, such as choosing a provider, writing sample code for interaction, or configuration instructions. Where would you like to start?","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_031369d1ef8110be0069da4cd852cc8194b54d2dfce42a1b22\"}"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openai","model":"gpt-4.1-mini","usage":{"input":106,"output":256,"cacheRead":11648,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":12010,"cost":{"input":0.0000424,"output":0.00040960000000000004,"cacheRead":0.0011648000000000001,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0016168000000000003}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775914199492}}
